The paper deals with gossip algorithms in networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also mentions sensor networks, peer-to-peer networks, and content distribution networks, which fall under distributed computing (cs.DC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the stopping time of network coded protocols, which is a performance metric in control systems (cs.SY).
